<font color="#00FF00">Season 02 Episode 01a</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">"Intern For The Worse"</font>
Precisely Synchronized by <font color="#00FF00">srjanapala</font>

00:33.975 --> 00:37.093
♪

00:37.118 --> 00:38.882
♪

00:38.953 --> 00:41.554
[bell rings]

00:41.640 --> 00:45.257
♪

00:45.468 --> 00:47.703
Today is the fifth grade
internship fair,

00:47.773 --> 00:51.234
and Clyde and I are making sure
to put our best foot forward.

00:51.398 --> 00:54.019
'Cause there's only
one place we wanna work...

00:54.867 --> 00:55.834
[snoring]

00:55.866 --> 00:57.772
BOTH: Flip's Food & Fuel.

00:57.882 --> 01:00.398
Good morrow, fine sir.
I'm Clyde McBride,

01:00.476 --> 01:02.289
and this is my associate,
Lincoln Loud.

01:02.351 --> 01:05.546
Together, we're known as...
BOTH: Clincoln McCloud.

01:05.635 --> 01:07.502
We're a team.

01:08.382 --> 01:09.898
We'd love the opportunity

01:09.945 --> 01:12.007
to work at your fine
establishment...

01:12.179 --> 01:13.367
BOTH: as a team.

01:13.414 --> 01:14.343
Two for one?

01:14.398 --> 01:16.460
Now you're speaking
Flip's language.

01:16.510 --> 01:19.179
If you peruse our joint
resume, I think you'll find...

01:19.242 --> 01:20.289
Never mind that.

01:20.347 --> 01:22.156
Either of you got
a criminal record?

01:22.234 --> 01:23.882
- BOTH: No.
- You're hired.

01:23.976 --> 01:25.593
BOTH: Woo-hoo!

01:25.703 --> 01:27.984
We'll get to see where
the nacho cheese comes from.

01:28.054 --> 01:30.164
And read the comics as
soon as they're delivered.

01:30.242 --> 01:32.359
And use the Flippy machine.

01:32.414 --> 01:34.493
BOTH: Ooh, Flippys...

01:34.906 --> 01:36.757
Hey, Stinkin' McFartcloud,

01:36.828 --> 01:40.398
your internship started
ten seconds ago!

01:42.820 --> 01:45.593
See, boys? Across and down.

01:45.679 --> 01:48.674
That's the technique.
Now your turn.

01:49.234 --> 01:50.531
But we're out of window cleaner.

01:50.593 --> 01:52.022
Should I go in
the store and get some?

01:52.046 --> 01:53.070
You kiddin' me?

01:53.140 --> 01:55.640
That stuff costs
40 cents a gallon.

01:55.703 --> 01:57.436
Here.
[forehead squeaks]

01:59.992 --> 02:02.859
FLIP: Okay, we covered
the cash register,

02:02.937 --> 02:05.593
the gas pumps,
and stackin' the jerky.

02:05.703 --> 02:07.062
Last thing you need to know

02:07.125 --> 02:09.420
is how to adjust
the expiration date.

02:09.523 --> 02:10.562
There we go.

02:10.586 --> 02:12.218
- [marker squeaking]
- Now it's good 'till Christmas.

02:12.242 --> 02:13.602
Isn't that against the law?

02:13.648 --> 02:16.836
Did I say it was time for a Q&A?

02:18.133 --> 02:21.086
Now, you boys think
you're ready to take charge?

02:21.156 --> 02:22.719
- You bet!
- Yes, sir!

02:22.813 --> 02:24.763
Good! As an extra incentive,

02:24.880 --> 02:28.864
whoever's doin' the best job is
gonna get promoted to manager.

02:28.958 --> 02:30.208
I'll be in the back.

02:30.235 --> 02:34.170
But Flip's eyes and ears
are everywhere.

02:34.708 --> 02:36.856
So, put on a good show, huh?

02:36.981 --> 02:39.856
But we're a team.
I don't wanna be your manager.

02:39.919 --> 02:42.099
Me, neither.
We're Clincoln McCloud.

02:42.153 --> 02:43.629
FLIP: Oh, I forgot one thing.

02:43.731 --> 02:47.817
The manager gets
the unlimited free Flippy cup.

02:49.966 --> 02:52.396
Free Flippys?
Big deal. Who cares?

02:52.435 --> 02:54.302
Yeah, what kind of
team would we be

02:54.356 --> 02:56.888
if we let something as petty
as an endless supply

02:56.919 --> 03:00.388
of the sweetest,
tastiest, frostiest...

03:00.435 --> 03:01.356
What was I saying?

03:01.419 --> 03:03.911
That we're not gonna let
anything come between us.

03:03.958 --> 03:05.584
Right.

03:05.739 --> 03:07.935
I'm just gonna wipe
down this counter.

03:08.028 --> 03:10.563
And I'm just gonna
clean off this case.

03:10.708 --> 03:13.286
- [glass squeaking]
- [glass squeaking]

03:13.372 --> 03:15.075
[service bell dings]

03:17.052 --> 03:18.169
BOTH: Welcome to Flip's.

03:18.232 --> 03:19.575
How can I help you?

03:19.716 --> 03:22.677
Uh, you can get out of my way.
I need to make a tinkle.

03:22.771 --> 03:23.785
You can help me.

03:23.810 --> 03:25.583
Fill 'er up. Premium unleaded.

03:25.653 --> 03:27.105
I'm on it.

03:27.427 --> 03:29.942
Gas for your car
and gas for you.

03:30.185 --> 03:33.122
Ooh, beef jerky? Sweet.

03:33.174 --> 03:35.308
Keep up the good work, brother!

03:36.981 --> 03:40.294
Aah! How is anyone supposed
to tinkle in there?

03:40.356 --> 03:42.606
It is disgusting.

03:42.677 --> 03:44.056
I'm on it.

03:44.973 --> 03:47.184
- [cleaner spritzing]
- [squeegee squeaking]

03:47.247 --> 03:48.271
[toilet flushes]

03:48.310 --> 03:50.966
[gasps] Clyde, the powder
room was a delight.

03:51.052 --> 03:53.341
Five stars. Much better.

03:55.997 --> 03:57.349
BOTH: Have a Flippy day!

03:57.403 --> 03:59.396
BOTH: Keep up
the good work, boys!

03:59.583 --> 04:02.497
Look, I want you to know I'm
not trying to compete with you.

04:02.544 --> 04:04.052
I was just helping a customer.

04:04.099 --> 04:05.942
Oh, totally. Same with me.

04:05.997 --> 04:07.849
Clincoln McCloud. We're a team.

04:07.911 --> 04:08.880
- [microwave dings]
- [loud banging]

04:08.905 --> 04:11.343
OLD LADY: Oh, darn thing
is on the fritz!

04:11.368 --> 04:12.281
BOTH: I'm on it!

04:12.306 --> 04:13.666
- Hey, heat it up!
- [fist banging]

04:13.721 --> 04:15.304
BOTH: At your service, ma'am!

04:15.437 --> 04:16.562
What's the trouble?

04:16.601 --> 04:18.450
Your microwave is broken,

04:18.521 --> 04:21.411
leaving me as cold
as my burrito.

04:21.543 --> 04:23.661
I can heat this up
for you in a jiffy.

04:23.755 --> 04:25.530
[hand dryer whirring]

04:28.505 --> 04:30.490
I thought you said a jiffy.

04:30.568 --> 04:32.247
Allow me.

04:32.333 --> 04:33.888
Give her some gas, ma'am.

04:33.966 --> 04:37.411
[engine revving]

04:41.240 --> 04:43.974
What a good little employee.

04:44.138 --> 04:46.091
Have a Flippy day!

04:46.240 --> 04:47.318
Sorry for butting in,

04:47.375 --> 04:49.654
but, again, just trying
to help the customer.

04:49.935 --> 04:52.124
Oh, no, of course.

04:52.318 --> 04:56.361
♪

04:56.524 --> 04:58.397
Does anybody work here?

04:58.524 --> 05:00.462
I'd like to buy
some gas station pizza.

05:00.524 --> 05:01.938
I'm on it.

05:02.024 --> 05:05.170
You can help the next
customer... partner.

05:05.415 --> 05:07.844
- But...
- [horn honks]

05:08.579 --> 05:10.251
KIDS: Woo! Woo! Woo! Woo!

05:10.282 --> 05:11.129
[cheering]

05:11.154 --> 05:13.383
Got a massive order
for you, Clydesdale.

05:14.680 --> 05:16.290
- I'm on it!
- Hey there, partner.

05:16.340 --> 05:18.126
Looks like you could
use an assist.

05:18.180 --> 05:20.508
Oh, no, I got this, partner.

05:20.563 --> 05:22.946
You can help the next customer.

05:23.235 --> 05:25.712
- Oh, thanks, Clyde!
- You're the best.

05:25.766 --> 05:27.852
No problem, ladies.
Just doin' my job.

05:27.877 --> 05:28.780
MARGO: Yeah, yeah.

05:28.805 --> 05:30.290
Can you hold my dog,
Lynn-sanity?

05:30.346 --> 05:33.032
I gotta take a wicked dump.
No, Margo.

05:33.087 --> 05:36.110
You cannot go number two
until we are number one.

05:36.196 --> 05:38.337
[stomach gurgles]

05:38.462 --> 05:40.696
FLIP: Interns, assemble!

05:40.844 --> 05:43.712
I've made my decision
about which of you

05:43.789 --> 05:45.274
to promote to manager.

05:45.383 --> 05:46.611
BOTH: Who is it? Who is it?

05:46.688 --> 05:48.938
Eh, you're both showin'
some good hustle.

05:49.008 --> 05:54.217
But I'm gonna give
the edge to-o-o-o-o...

05:54.287 --> 05:56.922
- McBride!
- Yes!

05:57.092 --> 05:59.310
Congratulations.

05:59.514 --> 06:01.482
I knew you were
competing with me.

06:01.545 --> 06:02.826
Well, you were competing, too.

06:02.889 --> 06:06.459
You swiped that burrito right
out of my hands, burrito swiper.

06:06.537 --> 06:09.256
You're the one who was showing
off with the bathroom cleaning.

06:09.318 --> 06:11.256
Potpourri? Seriously?

06:11.318 --> 06:13.639
It provides a soothing
environment for our customers.

06:13.701 --> 06:15.295
And I won't apologize for that.

06:15.332 --> 06:16.873
Now, if you'll excuse me,

06:16.912 --> 06:19.670
I have an unlimited
free Flippy cup to fill...

06:19.764 --> 06:21.012
and refill.

06:21.115 --> 06:22.514
Grrrr!

06:22.616 --> 06:24.626
It's not fair, Flip.

06:24.712 --> 06:27.798
I've been working
just as hard as Clyde.

06:27.954 --> 06:29.704
That cup should be mine.

06:29.767 --> 06:31.523
I hear what you're
sayin', chief.

06:31.625 --> 06:34.525
Uh, you know, I do happen
to have an opening

06:34.572 --> 06:36.884
for a supervising manager.

06:36.986 --> 06:39.197
Technically the cup
would go to him.

06:39.222 --> 06:40.204
[gasps]

06:40.229 --> 06:42.814
But you're gonna have to show
me you deserve the gig.

06:42.915 --> 06:45.134
What do I have to do?
I'll do anything.

06:46.782 --> 06:49.274
Ugh! I think I found the clog.

06:49.439 --> 06:51.556
There's my missin' sock.

06:55.728 --> 06:58.236
No sense in wastin' good cheese.

06:58.385 --> 07:00.767
[slurping] Ahhhh...

07:00.931 --> 07:03.743
Sorry, chief,
we're doin' some restructuring.

07:03.807 --> 07:07.618
Say hello to your new
supervising manager.

07:07.665 --> 07:11.114
♪

07:11.200 --> 07:13.161
[flashbulb pops]

07:13.396 --> 07:15.200
I hear what
you're sayin', chief.

07:15.269 --> 07:19.192
You know, I do happen to have
another position available.

07:19.286 --> 07:22.291
Senior supervising manager.
[gasps]

07:22.385 --> 07:24.401
You'd get your cup back.

07:24.494 --> 07:26.197
What do I have to do?
I'll do anything.

07:26.260 --> 07:31.383
♪

07:31.485 --> 07:33.277
- [teeth chomping]
- CLYDE: [screams]

07:33.372 --> 07:35.098
[slurping] [sighs]

07:37.124 --> 07:38.323
[slurping]

07:38.425 --> 07:43.428
♪

07:43.530 --> 07:44.963
- [flies buzzing]
- Ugh!

07:45.899 --> 07:47.143
- [raccoon growls]
- LINCOLN: [screams]

07:47.167 --> 07:48.452
Oof!

07:48.535 --> 07:50.764
- [sighs] Hey?
- [loud thud]

07:50.819 --> 07:55.607
♪

07:55.709 --> 07:57.342
[sniffing]

07:57.444 --> 08:07.491
♪

08:07.694 --> 08:09.623
Oh, yeah, that's nice.

08:09.748 --> 08:12.014
[slurping] [sighs]

08:15.662 --> 08:16.895
- [scissors snip]
- [screams]

08:16.997 --> 08:18.330
- [hand "pops"]
- [sighs]

08:18.432 --> 08:21.084
♪

08:21.272 --> 08:23.373
Ah, too many Flippys! Gotta pee!

08:23.631 --> 08:26.022
Wait, I have to go, too.
Gimme that key!

08:26.100 --> 08:27.670
Sorry, I got first dibs.

08:27.702 --> 08:31.170
Don't forget, I'm executive
senior supervising manager.

08:31.248 --> 08:34.525
Yeah, but I'm senior executive
supervising manager.

08:34.602 --> 08:36.746
- I outrank you.
- Nuh-uh!

08:36.840 --> 08:38.770
Yuh-huh! I had it first!

08:38.832 --> 08:41.318
[grunts]
Come on, I'm warning you!

08:41.421 --> 08:43.075
BOTH: [punching, kicking]

08:43.136 --> 08:44.559
- Let go!
- I had it first!

08:44.614 --> 08:46.606
- Let go!
- No way, man!

08:46.707 --> 08:48.082
I've had it with you.

08:48.121 --> 08:50.723
You're fired! You can't fire me.

08:50.770 --> 08:53.356
I'm firing you. FLIP: Oh, yeah.

08:53.450 --> 08:55.676
Sure, sure, sure, sure,
I can go fishin'.

08:55.801 --> 08:58.887
I got two bozo interns
workin' their tails off

08:58.965 --> 09:01.296
tryin' to get promoted. [laughs]

09:01.429 --> 09:03.984
Amazing what a kid'll
do for free Flippys.

09:04.046 --> 09:05.523
[laughing]

09:05.609 --> 09:06.890
Holy nachos!

09:06.960 --> 09:08.890
Flip's been playing
us for fools.

09:09.023 --> 09:10.476
I'm really sorry, Lincoln.

09:10.530 --> 09:13.484
I let my love of Flippys get in
the way of our friendship.

09:13.577 --> 09:14.827
Me, too, Clyde.

09:14.882 --> 09:17.390
Can we please go back to
being Clincoln McCloud?

09:17.460 --> 09:18.773
You know it, buddy.

09:20.554 --> 09:21.984
And now that we're a team again,

09:22.023 --> 09:23.382
I think I know how to spend

09:23.437 --> 09:25.530
the last few hours
of our internship.

09:25.601 --> 09:28.934
- Updating our joint resume?
- Nope. Better.

09:30.017 --> 09:31.703
Oh, interns?

09:31.805 --> 09:35.743
I've got a special taxidermy
job for one of you.

09:35.814 --> 09:37.970
There's a promotion in it.
[flies buzzing]

09:38.079 --> 09:39.626
Uh, sorry, Flip.

09:39.673 --> 09:41.446
We've done a little
restructuring,

09:41.509 --> 09:44.017
and from now on,
we're calling the shots.

09:44.087 --> 09:47.392
I think all those Flippys
have given you brain freeze.

09:47.454 --> 09:48.853
Back to work, boys!

09:48.939 --> 09:52.598
- Shall we show him, Clincoln?
- Indeed, McCloud.

09:52.989 --> 09:54.879
Thanks to our senior positions,

09:54.957 --> 09:57.614
we had access to all
the store security footage.

09:57.684 --> 10:00.432
And we'd hate to see
this get on the internet.

10:00.534 --> 10:04.596
♪

10:04.642 --> 10:08.705
♪

10:08.779 --> 10:11.807
♪

10:11.832 --> 10:15.627
♪

10:15.695 --> 10:17.072
All right, enough!

10:17.142 --> 10:19.244
What'll take for
this to go away?

10:19.290 --> 10:20.704
I'll do anything!

10:22.456 --> 10:25.290
BOTH: [slurping]

10:25.392 --> 10:27.058
[snapping fingers]

10:29.496 --> 10:31.229
- [teeth chomping]
- [screams]

10:31.331 --> 10:36.569
♪

10:36.663 --> 10:38.269
[raccoon growls, chitters]

10:38.405 --> 10:41.210
- FLIP: [screaming]
- BOTH: [laughing]

10:43.644 --> 10:45.176
[racoon chittering]

10:46.713 --> 10:49.305
BOTH: [slurping]
To Clincoln McCloud!

10:49.406 --> 10:51.216
Cheers!
[horn honks]

10:51.318 --> 10:52.617
KIDS: [chanting]
We're number one!

10:52.641 --> 10:54.047
Time for number two!

10:54.121 --> 10:57.055
We're number one!
Time for number two!

10:57.109 --> 10:59.057
- [toilet flushes]
- Hallelujah!

10:59.159 --> 11:01.849
Phew! Sorry about the mess.

11:01.959 --> 11:02.864
No problem.

11:02.889 --> 11:05.342
We've got people who
take care of that for us.

11:05.435 --> 11:07.982
- Oh, Flip?
- What?

11:08.107 --> 11:10.435
[growling, muttering]

11:13.077 --> 11:14.944
Holy nachos!
